To run system A, please do the following:

0. Start the message manager, this is the common steps for system A B and C. 
   so you can leave these two console running for System B and C, please note that repeat these command will cause RMI port binding exception.

open a console, and type commands:
> rmiregistry
Open another console and type command:
> cd a3a
> java MessageManager

1. Start components
Start the components in console (on mac os):
> cd a3a
> ./startSystemA.sh 

2. Operate the system
After step 0 and 1, three java consoles() will pop up, and show the message sending and recieving between sensor/console/controller.
Use the security console(the console you run the ./startSystemA.sh ) to arm/disarm (type 1 and enter in the console) the intrusion detection system. You will see alarm message show or stop in console.